19// This class holds data required during deoptimization. It does not have its
20// own instance type.
21class DeoptimizationLiteralArray : public TrustedWeakFixedArray {
22 public:
23 // Getters for literals. These include runtime checks that the pointer was not
24 // cleared, if the literal was held weakly.
25 inline Tagged<Object> get(int index) const;
26 inline Tagged<Object> get(PtrComprCageBase cage_base, int index) const;
27
28 // TODO(jgruber): Swap these names around. It's confusing that this
29 // WeakFixedArray subclass redefines `get` with different semantics.
30 inline Tagged<MaybeObject> get_raw(int index) const;
31
32 // Setter for literals. This will set the object as strong or weak depending
33 // on InstructionStream::IsWeakObjectInOptimizedCode.
34 inline void set(int index, Tagged<Object> value);
35
36 DECL_CAST(DeoptimizationLiteralArray)
37
38 OBJECT_CONSTRUCTORS(DeoptimizationLiteralArray, TrustedWeakFixedArray);
39};

41enum class DeoptimizationLiteralKind {
42 kObject,
43 kNumber,
44 kSignedBigInt64,
45 kUnsignedBigInt64,
46 kInvalid,
47
48 // These kinds are used by wasm only (as unoptimized JS doesn't have these
49 // types).
50 // TODO(mliedtke): Add support for S128 / SIMD.
51 kWasmI31Ref,
52 kWasmInt32,
53 kWasmFloat,
54 kWasmDouble = kNumber,
55 kWasmInt64 = kSignedBigInt64,
56};
57
58// A deoptimization literal during code generation. For JS this is transformed
59// into a heap object after code generation. For wasm the DeoptimizationLiteral
60// is directly used by the deoptimizer.
61class DeoptimizationLiteral {
62 public:
63 DeoptimizationLiteral()
64 : kind_(DeoptimizationLiteralKind::kInvalid), object_() {}
65 explicit DeoptimizationLiteral(Handle<Object> object)
66 : kind_(DeoptimizationLiteralKind::kObject), object_(object) {
67 CHECK(!object_.is_null());
68 }
69 explicit DeoptimizationLiteral(float number)
70 : kind_(DeoptimizationLiteralKind::kWasmFloat), float_(number) {}
71 explicit DeoptimizationLiteral(double number)
72 : kind_(DeoptimizationLiteralKind::kNumber), number_(number) {}
73 explicit DeoptimizationLiteral(int64_t signed_bigint64)
74 : kind_(DeoptimizationLiteralKind::kSignedBigInt64),
75 int64_(signed_bigint64) {}
76 explicit DeoptimizationLiteral(uint64_t unsigned_bigint64)
77 : kind_(DeoptimizationLiteralKind::kUnsignedBigInt64),
78 uint64_(unsigned_bigint64) {}
79 explicit DeoptimizationLiteral(int32_t int32)
80 : kind_(DeoptimizationLiteralKind::kWasmInt32), int64_(int32) {}
81 explicit DeoptimizationLiteral(Tagged<Smi> smi)
82 : kind_(DeoptimizationLiteralKind::kWasmI31Ref), int64_(smi.value()) {}
83
84 Handle<Object> object() const { return object_; }
85
86 bool operator==(const DeoptimizationLiteral& other) const {
87 if (kind_ != other.kind_) {
88 return false;
89 }
90 switch (kind_) {
91 case DeoptimizationLiteralKind::kObject:
92 return object_.equals(other.object_);
93 case DeoptimizationLiteralKind::kNumber:
94 return base::bit_cast<uint64_t>(number_) ==
95 base::bit_cast<uint64_t>(other.number_);
96 case DeoptimizationLiteralKind::kWasmI31Ref:
97 case DeoptimizationLiteralKind::kWasmInt32:
98 case DeoptimizationLiteralKind::kSignedBigInt64:
99 return int64_ == other.int64_;
100 case DeoptimizationLiteralKind::kUnsignedBigInt64:
101 return uint64_ == other.uint64_;
102 case DeoptimizationLiteralKind::kInvalid:
103 return true;
104 case DeoptimizationLiteralKind::kWasmFloat:
105 return base::bit_cast<uint32_t>(float_) ==
106 base::bit_cast<uint32_t>(other.float_);
107 }
108 UNREACHABLE();
109 }
110
111 Handle<Object> Reify(Isolate* isolate) const;
112
113#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
114 double GetDouble() const {
115 DCHECK_EQ(kind_, DeoptimizationLiteralKind::kWasmDouble);
116 return number_;
117 }
118
119 float GetFloat() const {
120 DCHECK_EQ(kind_, DeoptimizationLiteralKind::kWasmFloat);
121 return float_;
122 }
123
124 int64_t GetInt64() const {
125 DCHECK_EQ(kind_, DeoptimizationLiteralKind::kWasmInt64);
126 return int64_;
127 }
128
129 int32_t GetInt32() const {
130 DCHECK_EQ(kind_, DeoptimizationLiteralKind::kWasmInt32);
131 return static_cast<int32_t>(int64_);
132 }
133
134 Tagged<Smi> GetSmi() const {
135 DCHECK_EQ(kind_, DeoptimizationLiteralKind::kWasmI31Ref);
136 return Smi::FromInt(static_cast<int>(int64_));
137 }
138#endif
139
140 void Validate() const {
141 CHECK_NE(kind_, DeoptimizationLiteralKind::kInvalid);
142 }
143
144 DeoptimizationLiteralKind kind() const {
145 Validate();
146 return kind_;
147 }
148
149 private:
150 DeoptimizationLiteralKind kind_;
151
152 union {
153 Handle<Object> object_;
154 double number_;
155 float float_;
156 int64_t int64_;
157 uint64_t uint64_;
158 };
159};

161// The DeoptimizationFrameTranslation is the on-heap representation of
162// translations created during code generation in a (zone-allocated)
163// DeoptimizationFrameTranslationBuilder. The translation specifies how to
164// transform an optimized frame back into one or more unoptimized frames.
165enum class TranslationOpcode;
166class DeoptimizationFrameTranslation : public TrustedByteArray {
167 public:
168 DECL_CAST(DeoptimizationFrameTranslation)
169
170 struct FrameCount {
171 int total_frame_count;
172 int js_frame_count;
173 };
174
175 class Iterator;
176
177#ifdef V8_USE_ZLIB
178 // Constants describing compressed DeoptimizationFrameTranslation layout. Only
179 // relevant if
180 // --turbo-compress-frame-translation is enabled.
181 static constexpr int kUncompressedSizeOffset = 0;
182 static constexpr int kUncompressedSizeSize = kInt32Size;
183 static constexpr int kCompressedDataOffset =
184 kUncompressedSizeOffset + kUncompressedSizeSize;
185 static constexpr int kDeoptimizationFrameTranslationElementSize = kInt32Size;
186#endif // V8_USE_ZLIB
187
188 inline uint32_t get_int(int offset) const;
189 inline void set_int(int offset, uint32_t value);
190
191#ifdef ENABLE_DISASSEMBLER
192 void PrintFrameTranslation(
193 std::ostream& os, int index,
194 Tagged<DeoptimizationLiteralArray> literal_array) const;
195#endif
196
197 OBJECT_CONSTRUCTORS(DeoptimizationFrameTranslation, TrustedByteArray);
198};

200class DeoptTranslationIterator {
201 public:
202 DeoptTranslationIterator(base::Vector<const uint8_t> buffer, int index);
203
204 int32_t NextOperand();
205
206 uint32_t NextOperandUnsigned();
207
208 DeoptimizationFrameTranslation::FrameCount EnterBeginOpcode();
209
210 TranslationOpcode NextOpcode();
211
212 TranslationOpcode SeekNextJSFrame();
213 TranslationOpcode SeekNextFrame();
214
215 bool HasNextOpcode() const;
216
217 void SkipOperands(int n) {
218 for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) NextOperand();
219 }
220
221 private:
222 TranslationOpcode NextOpcodeAtPreviousIndex();
223 uint32_t NextUnsignedOperandAtPreviousIndex();
224 void SkipOpcodeAndItsOperandsAtPreviousIndex();
225
226 std::vector<int32_t> uncompressed_contents_;
227 const base::Vector<const uint8_t> buffer_;
228 int index_;
229
230 // This decrementing counter indicates how many more times to read operations
231 // from the previous translation before continuing to move the index forward.
232 int remaining_ops_to_use_from_previous_translation_ = 0;
233
234 // An index into buffer_ for operations starting at a previous BEGIN, which
235 // can be used to read operations referred to by MATCH_PREVIOUS_TRANSLATION.
236 int previous_index_ = 0;
237
238 // When starting a new MATCH_PREVIOUS_TRANSLATION operation, we'll need to
239 // advance the previous_index_ by this many steps.
240 int ops_since_previous_index_was_updated_ = 0;
241};

251// DeoptimizationData is a fixed array used to hold the deoptimization data for
252// optimized code. It also contains information about functions that were
253// inlined. If N different functions were inlined then the first N elements of
254// the literal array will contain these functions.
255//
256// It can be empty.
257class DeoptimizationData : public ProtectedFixedArray {
258 public:
259 // Layout description. Indices in the array.
260 static const int kFrameTranslationIndex = 0;
261 static const int kInlinedFunctionCountIndex = 1;
262 static const int kLiteralArrayIndex = 2;
263 static const int kOsrBytecodeOffsetIndex = 3;
264 static const int kOsrPcOffsetIndex = 4;
265 static const int kOptimizationIdIndex = 5;
266 static const int kSharedFunctionInfoWrapperIndex = 6;
267 static const int kInliningPositionsIndex = 7;
268 static const int kDeoptExitStartIndex = 8;
269 static const int kEagerDeoptCountIndex = 9;
270 static const int kLazyDeoptCountIndex = 10;
271 static const int kFirstDeoptEntryIndex = 11;
272
273 // Offsets of deopt entry elements relative to the start of the entry.
274 static const int kBytecodeOffsetRawOffset = 0;
275 static const int kTranslationIndexOffset = 1;
276 static const int kPcOffset = 2;
277#ifdef DEBUG
278 static const int kNodeIdOffset = 3;
279 static const int kDeoptEntrySize = 4;
280#else // DEBUG
281 static const int kDeoptEntrySize = 3;
282#endif // DEBUG
283
284// Simple element accessors.
285#define DECL_ELEMENT_ACCESSORS(name, type) \
286 inline type name() const; \
287 inline void Set##name(type value);
288
289 DECL_ELEMENT_ACCESSORS(FrameTranslation,
290 Tagged<DeoptimizationFrameTranslation>)
291 DECL_ELEMENT_ACCESSORS(InlinedFunctionCount, Tagged<Smi>)
292 DECL_ELEMENT_ACCESSORS(LiteralArray, Tagged<DeoptimizationLiteralArray>)
293 DECL_ELEMENT_ACCESSORS(OsrBytecodeOffset, Tagged<Smi>)
294 DECL_ELEMENT_ACCESSORS(OsrPcOffset, Tagged<Smi>)
295 DECL_ELEMENT_ACCESSORS(OptimizationId, Tagged<Smi>)
296 DECL_ELEMENT_ACCESSORS(SharedFunctionInfoWrapper, Tagged<Object>)
297 DECL_ELEMENT_ACCESSORS(InliningPositions,
298 Tagged<TrustedPodArray<InliningPosition>>)
299 DECL_ELEMENT_ACCESSORS(DeoptExitStart, Tagged<Smi>)
300 DECL_ELEMENT_ACCESSORS(EagerDeoptCount, Tagged<Smi>)
301 DECL_ELEMENT_ACCESSORS(LazyDeoptCount, Tagged<Smi>)
302
303#undef DECL_ELEMENT_ACCESSORS
304
305 inline Tagged<Object> SharedFunctionInfo() const;
306
307// Accessors for elements of the ith deoptimization entry.
308#define DECL_ENTRY_ACCESSORS(name, type) \
309 inline type name(int i) const; \
310 inline void Set##name(int i, type value);
311
312 DECL_ENTRY_ACCESSORS(BytecodeOffsetRaw, Tagged<Smi>)
313 DECL_ENTRY_ACCESSORS(TranslationIndex, Tagged<Smi>)
314 DECL_ENTRY_ACCESSORS(Pc, Tagged<Smi>)
315#ifdef DEBUG
316 DECL_ENTRY_ACCESSORS(NodeId, Tagged<Smi>)
317#endif // DEBUG
318
319#undef DECL_ENTRY_ACCESSORS
320
321 // In case the innermost frame is a builtin continuation stub, then this field
322 // actually contains the builtin id. See uses of
323 // `Builtins::GetBuiltinFromBytecodeOffset`.
324 // TODO(olivf): Add some validation that callers do not misinterpret the
325 // result.
326 inline BytecodeOffset GetBytecodeOffsetOrBuiltinContinuationId(int i) const;
327
328 inline void SetBytecodeOffset(int i, BytecodeOffset value);
329
330 inline int DeoptCount() const;
331
332 static const int kNotInlinedIndex = -1;
333
334 // Returns the inlined function at the given position in LiteralArray, or the
335 // outer function if index == kNotInlinedIndex.
336 Tagged<class SharedFunctionInfo> GetInlinedFunction(int index);
337
338 // Allocates a DeoptimizationData.
339 static Handle<DeoptimizationData> New(Isolate* isolate,
340 int deopt_entry_count);
341 static Handle<DeoptimizationData> New(LocalIsolate* isolate,
342 int deopt_entry_count);
343
344 // Return an empty DeoptimizationData.
345 V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE static Handle<DeoptimizationData> Empty(Isolate* isolate);
346 V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE static Handle<DeoptimizationData> Empty(
347 LocalIsolate* isolate);
348
349 DECL_CAST(DeoptimizationData)
350
351#ifdef DEBUG
352 void Verify(Handle<BytecodeArray> bytecode) const;
353#endif
354#ifdef ENABLE_DISASSEMBLER
355 void PrintDeoptimizationData(std::ostream& os) const;
356#endif
357
358 private:
359 static int IndexForEntry(int i) {
360 return kFirstDeoptEntryIndex + (i * kDeoptEntrySize);
361 }
362
363 static int LengthFor(int entry_count) { return IndexForEntry(entry_count); }
364
365 OBJECT_CONSTRUCTORS(DeoptimizationData, ProtectedFixedArray);
366};
